# Next.js Frontend Conventions

## Page structure
- App Router pages: `app/<route>/page.tsx`
- Default export: page component (async for server, function for client)
- Layouts: `app/layout.tsx` — wraps all pages with header/footer/providers
- Admin routes: all protected via `apps/admin/middleware.ts` (check `admin_session` cookie)

## Client vs Server
- Add `'use client'` directive at top when using: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRouter`, `useSearchParams`, `useCart()`, event handlers
- Server components: fetch data directly (no hooks), prefer async
- Storefront homepage: server component fetching CMS via `getHomepage()`

## Data fetching (admin)
- Use `adminFetch` from `apps/admin/lib/admin-api.ts` — sets `credentials: 'include'`, handles 401 redirect
- API calls use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` from `apps/admin/lib/api.ts`
- Handle loading/error states: show loading skeleton or error message
- Forms: use `FormData` for image uploads, JSON for data

## Data fetching (storefront)
- Public API: `API_BASE_URL` from `apps/storefront/lib/api.ts`
- Zustand store: `apps/storefront/store/use-cart.ts` for cart state
- Toast: `useToast()` from `apps/storefront/components/toast-provider.tsx`

## Component patterns
- One component per file, named export matching filename
- Pass className prop for composability
- Use `ProductImage` component for all product images (handles fallback)
- Format prices with `formatVnd()` from `@/lib/format` (admin) or `@repo/shared` (storefront)

## Navigation
- Internal links: use `<Link href="...">` from 'next/link'
- External/admin-to-store: use `<a>` tags
- Breadcrumbs: `Trang chủ > Category > Product name`
